##Who was the first person to be genetically tested for new coronary pneumonia?

I-CAIJING

Linkage of three medical, bridge capital, direct health

After the first "unclassified coronavirus" was detected by a third-party testing agency, the hospital was informed only by telephone. Three days later, the second case report read "SARS coronavirus. ". No one thought at the time that it was a COVID-19 attack

Wen | Caijing reporter, Xinna, Wang Xiao Caijing reporter, Sun Aimin

Editor | Wang Xiao

A single-page Word document titled "Aaa Hot Situation Note" , dated December 30,2019, recorded the visit of two pneumonia patients in Wuhan. So far, they should be among the first to be tested for new coronavirus-infected pneumonia.

Who is the first case of infection or confirmed cases of the epidemic, there is no consensus, pending further confirmation of the authorities. According to a paper published in the Lancet on January 24,2020 by Cao Bin, vice president of the china-japan Friendship Hospital and other researchers, 41 early confirmed cases showed that the first patient with new coronavirus pneumonia developed symptoms on December 1,2019.

Zhang Zhi (not his real name) , 65, was one of the first patients to be diagnosed with NCP, according to the December 30,2019, file entry. He has retired and previously worked at the South China Seafood Market in downtown Wuhan. On December 13,2019, Zhang Zhi developed a fever due to a cold, with a body temperature as high as 39.1 °C and chills before fever, but without symptoms of nasal congestion, runny nose, dyspnea and cough.

He went to Wuhan Central Hospital and was given oral antibiotics by his doctor. Five days later, he still had a high fever, his wife Wang Li and he came back to the Central Hospital. On that day, he was admitted to the emergency ward.

According to a hospital record obtained by Caijing, Zhang Zhi was hospitalized on December 18,2019. He was diagnosed as "community acquired pneumonia and severe illness" on the same day, and other diagnoses included respiratory failure and diabetes.

After 4 days of routine anti-infective treatment, Zhang Zhi still had a high fever. At about 2:30 on 22 December 2019, he was transferred to the respiratory intensive care unit of Wuhan Central Hospital. A person familiar with the matter told the financial reporter that Zhang Zhi entered the breathing room in serious condition. Earlier, in the emergency ward, doctors had done some anti-infection treatment for him, using Amoxicillin clavulanate potassium, Oseltamivir and Loxson tablets symptomatic treatment.

Amoxicillin clavulanate potassium is an antibiotic used for diseases caused by sensitive bacterial infections, but not for viral infections; Oseltamivir is only effective for influenza viruses; and Lorazepam is used for antipyretic and analgesic treatment of acute upper airway inflammation.

But Zhang Zhi still has a high fever. "We were worried, why didn't the fever go down? " Said Wang Li, the hospital every few days to replace the new treatment drugs, are useless, also did not check out what is the reason.

When the doctor told Zhang that he needed to do other tests to identify the pathogen. At the time, no one would have guessed that this was an aggressive COVID-19 attack.

To identify the pathogen

At 1100 hours on December 24,2019, Wuhan Central Hospital took bronchoalveolar lavage samples for Zhang Zhi and sent them to a third-party testing institution for NGS testing.

NGS is a testing method that can sequence the genome of a sample and analyze the sequence information. It is regarded as the "gold standard" of detection. A breathing doctor at a wuhan-based Sanjia hospital explained that heavier patients in the department who could not be diagnosed after screening for common pathogens would consider doing such tests to identify the pathogens.

Not Wait to get the test results, "the husband has been unbearable, continued high fever, can not breathe, the body can not afford" , Wang Li recalled. In the early morning of December 25,2019, after signing out of the hospital, Wang Li took Zhang Zhi to the Tongji Hospital of the Tongji Medical College Tongji Medical College for better treatment.".

An employee of a wuhan-based genetic testing company explained that the test generally takes three working days to get results. By that date, Zhang's test results should have been sent back to Wuhan's Central Hospital on December 27,2019. The third-party testing agency, "did not dare to give a written report, just a phone call, said it is coronavirus. ". A medical staff member in the Emergency Department of Wuhan Central Hospital told Caijing.

At the time, there were no COVID-19 kits, only SARS kits. NGS is a more accurate way to identify viruses than kits and CT scans.

In a paper published in the Lancet on January 24,2020, Cao Bin, deputy director of the china-japan Friendship Hospital, and researchers from Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital and Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital, among others, analyzed 41 early confirmed cases of the disease, the first patient with NCP developed symptoms on 1 December 2019. The patient's family had no fever and respiratory symptoms, and the first patient was not epidemiologically associated with other patients thereafter.

"CAIJING" reporters obtained a material, confirmed that Zhang experienced the genetic test results for the "coronavirus unclassified. But in the information that has been made public, this "unclassified" has not been explicitly mentioned.

His test results were synced with those from Wuhan's Tung Chai Hospital. A staff member of the hospital confirmed to Caijing that he had received the patient's test results, but refused to disclose the specific time and follow-up treatment.

Hubei Province Integrated Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital aspiration and critical medical director Zhang Jixian, is regarded as the "outbreak reported the first person. ". She was rewarded for being the first to sound the alarm for epidemic prevention and control.

On December 26,2019, Zhang Jixian began to be on the alert after receiving several patients with similar symptoms in succession, and all of them ruled out the infection of known common pathogens. On December 27,2019, she reported the patient's condition to the director of operations, Xia Wenguang, the office of hospital sentiment and the medical department. The hospital then orally reported the patient's condition to the Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control in Wuhan.

A staff member of the Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Wuhan, who is in charge of the examination of infectious disease report cards, told Caijing that the initial hospitals may have reported the disease orally to the leaders of the Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control and Prevention, but has not filled in in the Infectious Disease Network direct report system, reports.

"Last Friday [ December 27,2019] , cases were reported from hospitals. ". A staff member of Wuhan CDC told Caijing on December 31,2019.

The next few days, Zhang Jixian again treated a number of similar patients. On December 29,2019, Zhang Jixian's hospital organized an expert consultation and reported directly to the Disease Control Office of Hubei Provincial Health Commission and the Disease Control Office of Wuhan Municipal Health Commission.

A doctor at Wuhan's Central Hospital told Caijing that he had heard about the report from the Hubei Hospital for the integration of traditional Chinese and Western medicine, but at the time they had treated only a few suspected patients. "We have tested out the virus, " he said.

During his stay, Zhang received three anti-infective drugs, Meropenem, Fluconazole and norvancomycin. But it's not getting any better.

"The first patient our hospital has received is not the first case of this epidemic, " a staff member of a department at Wuhan Central Hospital told Caijing.

Similar to Zhang, on 27 December 2019, close to 17:00, a patient was just transferred from the Department of Respiratory Medicine of Jiangxia District People's Hospital of Wuhan to Wuhan Central Hospital, anti-infective therapy was not effective: chest CT showed severe pneumonia.

According to the information obtained by CAIJING reporter, the 41-year-old male patient developed fever around December 16,2019, with a maximum body temperature of 39.5 °C, after 6 days of fever in December 22,2019 in Jiangxia District People's Hospital, 5 days of inhalation treatment, anti-infection treatment, temperature control, transferred to Wuhan Central Hospital.

At 18:00 p.m. on Dec. 27,2019, the patient was intensive-care unit, who was also scheduled for bronchoscopic lavage for NGS. Three days later, on December 30,2019, the hospital received the test results from a third-party company. The test report said "SARS coronavirus" . The results were first reported to the hospital's Public Health Department and the hospital's sensory control department.

On 28 December 2019, four fever patients associated with the south China seafood market were admitted to the back Lake District of Wuhan Central Hospital. The next day, the emergency department reported the four cases to the hospital's Public Health Department, which reported them to the Han River CDC.

On the afternoon of December 30,2019, Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, posted the test report on a wechat group for medical professionals.

The last three days

On the morning of December 29,2019, doctors at Wuhan Tongji Hospital informed Chang Chih-chia that the patient needed to be transferred to Jinyintan Hospital, and advised his family to wear masks, "in case the disease is contagious. ". The doctor was wearing a mask, Wang recalls.

At that time, Zhang Zhi's condition continued to deteriorate and he had already started to be intubated. A succession of ambulances could not be transferred because they were not equipped to do so, and they had to wait until 30 December 2019. Wang Li recalls: That day, there are also four or five patients have been transferred to the hospital.

The first four cases were reported on December 29,2019, according to a paper published in the The New England Journal of Medicine on January 29,2020 by researchers from the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the Hubei Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention and the University of Hong Kong, the four cases were reported through the "unexplained pneumonia surveillance system" established after SARS in 2003, and were all related to the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan.

The paper therefore listed December 8,2019, as the first day of onset of NCP, with one case on the day but no history of exposure to the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan.

After 22 days, on the evening of December 30,2019, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued an emergency notice with the theme of "report on the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause. ". According to an urgent notice from a superior, pneumonia patients of unknown origin have been found in the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, it said.

On December 31,2019, around 1:00 pm, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission announced that 27 cases had been found, of which 7 cases were in serious condition. "through multi-analysis, the above-mentioned cases are viral pneumonia. ".

On December 30,2019, Zhang was admitted to Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital for Infectious Disease Patients after tests concluded that the virus was unclassified. Wang Li and her husband were separated by the door and never saw each other again. The doctor told Wang that Zhang was suffering from a viral pneumonia disease. "He is in a serious condition. You have to wait 24 hours for the notification. His life may be in danger at any time. "

Since then Wang Li has not been any news, the family can only hope that one day can get in touch with the doctor, Zhang Zhi to explore a bit of information. They fell into the empty, "No bottom, the whole family is not bottom, " Wang Li said: "It is difficult. "

It wasn't until the sixth day of the first lunar month (January 30,2020) that Wang received a call from her doctor. "At 7:20, the first call said that her husband in the rescue, " Wang Li accurately recalled the time of the call, "20 minutes later and call, people have gone.

Wang Li offered to go to the hospital for her husband to send a dress, was rejected. The doctor told: The family can not come, 10 am can come to get the death certificate, the doctor again warned: "This disease may be contagious. ".

On the morning of December 31,2019, a team of experts sent by the National Health Commission arrived in Wuhan to carry out testing and verification. At 1 pm that day, a staff member of the Wuhan CDC told Caijing that the city CDC had tested the samples and the provincial CDC was organizing experts to review the samples.

"Is it dangerous to have pneumonia cases of unknown origin in the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan? " A Wuhan Virologist transferred to Guangzhou received a call from his family early in the morning, asking if there was any danger.

The South China Seafood Market is less than a five-minute walk from Wuhan's Special Care Hospital. Staff of the hospital told Caijing on December 31,2019 that some of the suspected patients appearing in the seafood market had sought medical treatment at the Central Hospital of Wuhan (Houhu Hospital area) and were later transferred to Jinyintan Hospital in Wuhan.

"As of February 11,2020, a total of 44,672 confirmed cases have been reported nationwide, with 0.2 percent of the cases occurring before December 31,2019, in Hubei Province, " said Zhang Yanping, a researcher with the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, so says a paper published in the February 17,2020, issue of the Chinese Journal of Epidemiology.

By December 31,2019, about 89 cases may have been reported in Hubei, according to the data in this paper.

On December 31,2019, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission reported that the above cases were from the viral pneumonia. "So far the investigation has found no significant human-to-human transmission and no medical staff infection. At present, the detection of pathogens and the investigation of the causes of infection is under way. At present, all cases have been treated in isolation, close contacts are being tracked and medical observation is being carried out, the south China Seafood City of the sanitary investigation and environmental health disposal is being carried out."

Fortunately, Zhang Zhi's family day-to-day care, but not infected, "just a pity, can not send him away. ".

On the last day of 2019, rumors of a possible SARS case in Wuhan were abuzz. Speculation that the "unexplained" pneumonia was SARS was quickly amplified by rumours.

The South China Seafood Wholesale Market in Wuhan remained open on that day. Although Zhang Zhi had retired before his death, he often went to the market to meet some acquaintances, chat and play cards. He usually went there more than 12 noon and returned home more than 5 p.m.

On that day, a seafood firm located in the western district of the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan told Caijing that it was open as usual at 7 am and would not be affected. At 3 pm, a shop on the east side of the seafood market was open as usual. "The situation is not as serious as it has been uploaded on the Internet. ".
